## Autonomous repository maintenance

- Use `@autonomous-maintainer-standalone` or `$autonomous-maintainer` only when the user explicitly requests repository-wide discovery and implementation, not for a single defined task.
- Preserve pre-existing uncommitted work and repository-specific instructions.
- Start with `mode=report` when authority, product intent, or safety boundaries are unclear.
- Do not use this workflow to push, merge, deploy, release, publish, rewrite history, handle secrets, or mutate production systems.
- Treat `.autonomous-maintainer/` for the standalone variant, or `.omx/maintenance/` and `.omx/ultragoal/` for the OMX variant, as durable run state; resume compatible active work instead of starting a competing run.
